summary: A person is interviewed, answering questions about food preferences, favorite songs, and their artistic abilities. They state they dislike seafood, and their favorite song to sing live is "Writing's On The Wall." They mention never having done yoga, that the best gig they've been to was the Gracie Abrams show, and that they are good at drawing and can paint a little bit.
transcript: 60 seconds with Role Model. What food can't you stand? Seafood. Seafood. Never had it but can't stand it. Can you handle spicy food? No. I'm from New England. Favorite song to sing live? Writing's On The Wall. Oh. Slut Era. It's kind of my new favorite. It's much better live. Yoga or gym? Gym. I've never done yoga. I ain't been in LA that long. Best gig you've ever been to? Gracie Abrams show. Are you good at drawing? I am good at drawing. That was like my whole childhood. I can paint a little bit. Maybe not anymore. Maybe not anymore. 0 check back for 60 seconds overtime.
